Project Identity: Golden Goose Tees Studio (v2.0)

This project is a high-end, world-class design studio for custom apparel and merchandise.
It is a transformation of a previous "Kiosk" app.

Core Directives

Aesthetic: "World Class," Apple-like, Premium.

Backgrounds: Deep Charcoal/Black (#0a0a0a) or rich dark gradients.

Accents: Gold (#D4AF37) and crisp White.

Typography: Clean, editorial, large headings (Sans-serif).

Interaction: Smooth Framer Motion transitions, glassmorphism, no "standard" HTML inputs (use styled custom UI).

Architecture:

Frontend: React + Vite + Tailwind CSS + Framer Motion.

Backend: Supabase (Auth, DB) + Printful API (Print-on-Demand).

Substrate Engine: The app must support MULTIPLE product categories (Apparel, Drinkware, Accessories) via a generic Product interface.

Single File Principle: Keep related logic self-contained. Use src/lib/utils.ts for shared helpers.

State Management (The Studio Flow):

Strict Modes: The UI must adhere to a specific state machine:
SELECT_PRODUCT -> CONFIGURE_VARIANTS -> EDIT_DESIGN -> PREVIEW -> CHECKOUT.

No Mode Mixing: Never show T-shirt tools when a Mug is selected.

Behavior:

T-Shirt First: While we support all items, T-Shirts are the "Golden Goose." The UI should prioritize them visually.

Substrate Awareness: The Design Editor must adapt its canvas shape (cylinder vs. flat) based on the selected product.

Tech Stack Rules

Use lucide-react for icons.

Use shadcn/ui patterns for components.

STRICT TypeScript usage. No any.

Folder Structure:

src/components/studio/: All design tool components (Canvas, ToolDock, etc.).

src/lib/printful/: All API integrations.

Always verify src/lib/types.ts matches the current product logic.
